### Hadith 1:698

*Narrated Zaid bin Thabit:*

Allah's Apostle made a small room in the month of Ramadan (Sa'id said,
"I think that Zaid bin Thabit said that it was made of a mat") and he
prayed there for a few nights, and so some of his companions prayed
behind him. When he came to know about it, he kept on sitting. In the
morning, he went out to them and said, "I have seen and understood what
you did. You should pray in your houses, for the best prayer of a person
is that which he prays in his house except the compulsory prayers."

